                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am an officer. In consequence of an information, I went to Lambeth, and found in the prisoner's room one gown, an umbrella, a muslin handkerchief, and an apron; and here are some other things, which I found in South Audley-street, where she had left them to be washed. (The things produced, and deposed to.) I also found a duplicate of a pair of stays.</p>
               <p>A WITNESS sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a servant to a pawnbroker; I have got a pair of stays, which I received from the prisoner on the 25th of February; I had known her before.</p>
               <p>(The stays deposed to.)</p>
               <p>Court to 
